CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776819790
OL,3,CHow close is Starmer to sacking
OL,4,Chimself?
OL,6,F4) Starmer's private office put
OL,7,Fpressure on Robbins to appoint his
OL,8,Fdirector of communications Matthew
OL,9,FDoyle as an ambassador but should keep
OL,10,Fthe then foreign secretary David Lammy
OL,11,Fin the dark;
OL,13,F5) UK Security Vetting's concerns
OL,14,Fabout appointing Mandelson were not
OL,15,Frelated to his friendship with the
OL,16,Fconvicted billionaire paedophile
OL,17,FJeffrey Epstein;
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776819790
OL,3,CHow close is Starmer to sacking
OL,4,Chimself?
OL,6,F6) The UK security services granted
OL,7,FMandelson even higher security
OL,8,Fclearance than even the foreign office
OL,9,Fhad done, namely STRAP status.
OL,11,FWhat emerges from all of this is a
OL,12,Fpicture of the prime minister and his
OL,13,Fteam trying to appoint Mandelson at
OL,14,Fall costs, and of vetting procedures
OL,15,Fthat are wholly inadequate.
OL,17,FWhat does not emerge is the notion
OL,18,Fthat Robbins had any culpability for
OL,19,Fthe worst appointment in modern
OL,20,Fpolitical history, that of Mandelson
OL,21,Fas US ambassador.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
