OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776819790
OL,3,CHow close is Starmer to sacking
OL,4,Chimself?
OL,6,FBut as bad for Starmer is that Robbins
OL,7,Fwas a highly credible witness, which
OL,8,Fleads to the inescapable conclusion
OL,9,Fthat he has been made a scapegoat by
OL,10,FStarmer, that he was doing his job
OL,11,Fproperly and that he should not have
OL,12,Fbeen dismissed.
OL,14,FThe point is that Robbins had no
OL,15,Fproper basis for blocking Mandelson,
OL,16,Fonce the PM had announced he would be
OL,17,Fappointed, especially given that the
OL,18,FPM had been informed by the Cabinet
OL,19,FOffice of Epstein and other serious
OL,20,Frisks BEFORE he appointed Mandelson.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
