OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776819790
OL,3,CHow close is Starmer to sacking
OL,4,Chimself?
OL,6,FStarmer gave Robbins the boot
OL,7,Fapparently for not having the
OL,8,Fimagination at the time to find a way
OL,9,Fto save the PM from his own
OL,10,Fcatastrophic decisions - even though
OL,11,FStarmer and his then chief of staff
OL,12,FMorgan McSweeney just wanted the FCDO
OL,13,Fto rush the vetting and rubber stamp
OL,14,Fthe appointment.
OL,16,FThe implications for Starmer's grip on
OL,17,Foffice are so obvious they do not bear
OL,18,Frepeating.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
